testprocedure.test-case-summary: This test procedure is called by a test case and is used to verify the SUTs support of the dlSectionPriorityQueueRequest dialog as an OC using variables provided by the calling test case. This procedure supports verification of requirements related to user need 2.3.5.10.16 [Need to View Section Plan Queue] and is used for both valid and invalid test cases.

testStep.functionId: Step 1 CONFIGURE: Determine the Application Layer Standard that will be used for this test. RECORD this information as: ApplicationLayerStandard: ${ApplicationLayerStandard}

Step 2 CONFIGURE: Determine the dialog performance requirement for Send Section Control Priority Queue Information Upon Request (NTRM 3.3.5.11.14.1}. RECORD this value as: TMDD_N101R1134_Send_Section_Control_Priority_Queue_Information_Upon_Request_Parameter = ${TMDD_N101R1134_Send_Section_Control_Priority_Queue_Information_Upon_Request_Parameter}

Step 3 CONFIGURE: Determine whether Restrictions - Device Queue is required by the specification. (NRTM 3.3.5.1.7.2.2.1). RECORD this information as: TMDD_N101R437_Restrictions___Device_Queue_Supported = ${TMDD_N101R437_Restrictions___Device_Queue_Supported}

Step 4 CONFIGURE: Determine whether Operator Identifier - Device Queue Acknowledge is required by the specification. (NRTM 3.3.5.1.7.2.2.2). RECORD this information as: TMDD_N101R438_Operator_Identifier___Device_Queue_Acknowledge_Supported = ${TMDD_N101R438_Operator_Identifier___Device_Queue_Acknowledge_Supported}

Step 5 CONFIGURE: Determine whether Unique Sequence Number is required by the specification. (NRTM 3.3.5.1.7.2.2.3). RECORD this information as: TMDD_N101R439_Unique_Sequence_Number_Supported = ${TMDD_N101R439_Unique_Sequence_Number_Supported}

Step 6 CONFIGURE: Determine whether Event Identifier - Device Queue is required by the specification. (NRTM 3.3.5.1.7.2.2.4). RECORD this information as: TMDD_N101R440_Event_Identifier___Device_Queue_Supported = ${TMDD_N101R440_Event_Identifier___Device_Queue_Supported}

Step 7 CONFIGURE: Determine whether Event Response Plan - Device Queue is required by the specification. (NRTM 3.3.5.1.7.2.2.5). RECORD this information as: TMDD_N101R441_Event_Response_Plan___Device_Queue_Supported = ${TMDD_N101R441_Event_Response_Plan___Device_Queue_Supported}

Step 8 CONFIGURE: Determine whether Request Start Date and Time - Device Queue is required by the specification. (NRTM 3.3.5.1.7.2.2.6). RECORD this information as: TMDD_N101R442_Request_Start_Date_and_Time___Device_Queue_Supported = ${TMDD_N101R442_Request_Start_Date_and_Time___Device_Queue_Supported}

Step 9 CONFIGURE: Determine whether Request Expiration Date and Time - Device Queue is required by the specification. (NRTM 3.3.5.1.7.2.2.7). RECORD this information as: TMDD_N101R443_Request_Expiration_Date_and_Time___Device_Queue_Supported = ${TMDD_N101R443_Request_Expiration_Date_and_Time___Device_Queue_Supported}

Step 10 CONFIGURE: Determine whether Signal Timing Mode - Section Queue is required by the specification. (NRTM 3.3.5.11.14.3.2.1). RECORD this information as: TMDD_N101R1138_Signal_Timing_Mode___Section_Queue_Supported = ${TMDD_N101R1138_Signal_Timing_Mode___Section_Queue_Supported}

Step 11 CONFIGURE: Determine whether Timing Pattern Identifier - Section Queue is required by the specification. (NRTM 3.3.5.11.14.3.2.2). RECORD this information as: TMDD_N101R1139_Timing_Pattern_Identifier___Section_Queue_Supported = ${TMDD_N101R1139_Timing_Pattern_Identifier___Section_Queue_Supported}

Step 12 CONFIGURE: Determine whether Offset Adjustment - Section Queue is required by the specification. (NRTM 3.3.5.11.14.3.2.3). RECORD this information as: TMDD_N101R1140_Offset_Adjustment___Section_Queue_Supported = ${TMDD_N101R1140_Offset_Adjustment___Section_Queue_Supported}

Step 13 CONFIGURE: Determine whether Restrictions - Error Report is required by the specification. (NRTM 3.3.1.4.1.2.1). RECORD this information as: TMDD_N101R15_Restrictions___Error_Report_Supported = ${TMDD_N101R15_Restrictions___Error_Report_Supported}
Step 14 CONFIGURE: Define the message that will be sent to the SUT. RECORD this information as: RequestMessage: ${RequestMessage}
Step 15 CONFIGURE: Determine whether an error response message is expected for this test. RECORD this information as: ErrorResponseExpected: ${ErrorResponseExpected}
Step 16 CONFIGURE: IF ErrorResponseExpected is true, determine the expected error code response for this test. RECORD this information as: ErrorTypeExpected: ${ErrorTypeExpected}

Step 17 REQUEST-RESPONSE-EC with the following parameters: DIALOG=dlSectionPriorityQueueRequest RESPONSETIMEREQUIRED=TMDD_N101R1134_Send_Section_Control_Priority_Queue_Information_Upon_Request_Parameter REQUESTMESSAGE = RequestMessage ERRORRESPONSEEXPECTED = ErrorResponseExpected ERRORTYPEEXPECTED = ErrorTypeExpected

Step 18 IF ErrorResponseExpected is not equal to TRUE THEN CONTINUE, OTHERWISE skip the following substeps. Note: If a verification step fails, then test execution will proceed at the next subsequent Post Condition step, if present. Otherwise, test execution will proceed to the final Exit step.
Step 18.1 VERIFY that a device-priority-queue-header data frame exists within message sectionPriorityQueueMsg.
Step 18.2 VERIFY that a device-id data element exists within each instance of data frame sectionPriorityQueueMsg.device-priority-queue-header
Step 18.3 VERIFY that a device-type data element exists within each instance of data frame sectionPriorityQueueMsg.device-priority-queue-header
Step 18.4 VERIFY that a current-device-priority data element exists within each instance of data frame sectionPriorityQueueMsg.device-priority-queue-header

Step 18.5 VERIFY that an organization-requesting data frame exists within each instance of data frame sectionPriorityQueueMsg.device-priority-queue-header.device-priority-queue-list.device-priority-queue-item

Step 18.6 VERIFY that a command-request-priority data element exists within each instance of data frame sectionPriorityQueueMsg.device-priority-queue-header.device-priority-queue-list.device-priority-queue-item
Step 18.7 VERIFY that a sectionPriorityQueueMsg message was received.
Step 18.8 VERIFY that a device-priority-queue-header data frame exists within message sectionPriorityQueueMsg.
Step 18.9 VERIFY that a section-request-command data element exists within message sectionPriorityQueueMsg.
Step 18.10 IF TMDD_N101R437_Restrictions___Device_Queue_Supported is equal to TRUE THEN CONTINUE; OTHERWISE skip the following substeps.
Step 18.10.1 VERIFY that a restrictions data frame exists within each instance of data frame sectionPriorityQueueMsg.device-priority-queue-header
Step 18.11 IF TMDD_N101R438_Operator_Identifier___Device_Queue_Acknowledge_Supported is equal to TRUE THEN CONTINUE; OTHERWISE skip the following substeps.

Step 18.11.1 VERIFY that an operator-id data element exists within each instance of data frame sectionPriorityQueueMsg.device-priority-queue-header.device-priority-queue-list.device-priority-queue-item
Step 18.12 IF TMDD_N101R439_Unique_Sequence_Number_Supported is equal to TRUE THEN CONTINUE; OTHERWISE skip the following substeps.
Step 18.12.1 VERIFY that a request-id data element exists within each instance of data frame sectionPriorityQueueMsg.device-priority-queue-header.device-priority-queue-list.device-priority-queue-item
Step 18.13 IF TMDD_N101R440_Event_Identifier___Device_Queue_Supported is equal to TRUE THEN CONTINUE; OTHERWISE skip the following substeps.
Step 18.13.1 VERIFY that an event-id data element exists within each instance of data frame sectionPriorityQueueMsg.device-priority-queue-header.device-priority-queue-list.device-priority-queue-item
Step 18.14 IF TMDD_N101R441_Event_Response_Plan___Device_Queue_Supported is equal to TRUE THEN CONTINUE; OTHERWISE skip the following substeps.

Step 18.14.1 VERIFY that a response-plan-id data element exists within each instance of data frame sectionPriorityQueueMsg.device-priority-queue-header.device-priority-queue-list.device-priority-queue-item
Step 18.15 IF TMDD_N101R442_Request_Start_Date_and_Time___Device_Queue_Supported is equal to TRUE THEN CONTINUE; OTHERWISE skip the following substeps.

Step 18.15.1 VERIFY that a command-start-time data frame exists within each instance of data frame sectionPriorityQueueMsg.device-priority-queue-header.device-priority-queue-list.device-priority-queue-item
Step 18.16 IF TMDD_N101R443_Request_Expiration_Date_and_Time___Device_Queue_Supported is equal to TRUE THEN CONTINUE; OTHERWISE skip the following substeps.

Step 18.16.1 VERIFY that a command-end-time data frame exists within each instance of data frame sectionPriorityQueueMsg.device-priority-queue-header.device-priority-queue-list.device-priority-queue-item
Step 18.17 IF TMDD_N101R1138_Signal_Timing_Mode___Section_Queue_Supported is equal to TRUE THEN CONTINUE; OTHERWISE skip the following substeps.
Step 18.17.1 VERIFY that a request-control-mode data element exists within each instance of data frame sectionPriorityQueueMsg.section-queue-parameters
Step 18.18 IF TMDD_N101R1139_Timing_Pattern_Identifier___Section_Queue_Supported is equal to TRUE THEN CONTINUE; OTHERWISE skip the following substeps.
Step 18.18.1 VERIFY that a timing-pattern-id data element exists within each instance of data frame sectionPriorityQueueMsg.section-queue-parameters
Step 18.19 IF TMDD_N101R1140_Offset_Adjustment___Section_Queue_Supported is equal to TRUE THEN CONTINUE; OTHERWISE skip the following substeps.
Step 18.19.1 VERIFY that a section-offset-adjustment data element exists within each instance of data frame sectionPriorityQueueMsg.section-queue-parameters
Step 18.20 VERIFY that the values within the RESPONSE message are correct per the TMDD standard and known operational conditions.

USER-VERIFY-MESSAGE.functionId: The User Verifies the message content

testStep.functionId: Step 19 IF ErrorResponseExpected is equal to TRUE THEN CONTINUE, OTHERWISE skip the following substeps. If a verification step fails, then test execution will proceed at the next subsequent Post Condition step, if present. Otherwise, test execution will proceed to the final Exit step.
Step 19.1 VERIFY that an errorReportMsg message was received.
Step 19.2 VERIFY that an organization-information data frame exists within message errorReportMsg.
Step 19.3 VERIFY that an organization-requesting data frame exists within message errorReportMsg.
Step 19.4 VERIFY that an error-code data element exists within message errorReportMsg.
Step 19.5 VERIFY that an error-text data element exists within message errorReportMsg.
Step 19.6 VERIFY that data element error-code is set to ErrorResponseTypeExpected.
Step 19.7 IF TMDD_N101R15_Restrictions___Error_Report_Supported is equal to TRUE THEN CONTINUE; OTHERWISE skip the following substeps.
Step 19.7.1 VERIFY that a restrictions data frame exists within message errorReportMsg.
Step 20 EXIT
